<h2 id="insulation-quality-the-unsung-hero-of-cold-chain">Insulation Quality: The Unsung Hero of Cold Chain</h2>

<p>You can have the best freezer in the world, but if your box is "leaking" cold air, your fuel bills will skyrocket and your engine will wear out faster. When checking a cold truck supplier in Malaysia, ask about their body-building process:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>FRP (Fiberglass Reinforced Plastic):</strong> Most modern cold trucks use this for the inner and outer skin. It’s light, durable, and hygienic.</li>
  <li><strong>Polyurethane (PU) Foam:</strong> This is the "meat" of the insulation. High-density PU foam is essential for maintaining deep-freeze temperatures.</li>
  <li><strong>Door Seals:</strong> This is the most common point of failure. Check the quality of the rubber gaskets. If you can see light through the door when it's closed, you're losing money.</li>
</ul>

