<h2 id="faq-common-questions-about-cold-trucks-in-malaysia">FAQ: Common Questions About Cold Trucks in Malaysia</h2>

<h3>Does a cold truck require a special permit?</h3>
<p>Yes, in Malaysia, commercial vehicles require an <strong>APAD</strong> permit. Most reputable cold truck suppliers will help you with the documentation, or we can advise you on the process during the financing stage.</p>

<h3>How often should I service the refrigeration unit?</h3>
<p>In our experience, you should have a minor service every 3-4 months and a major calibration once a year. Regular maintenance is much cheaper than an emergency repair on the highway.</p>

<h3>Can I finance just the refrigeration box if I already have the truck?</h3>
<p>Yes! We often help clients who want to "convert" a standard dry box truck into a cold truck by financing the insulation and refrigeration unit separately.</p>

